Privacy Policy for Ashvadhenu 

Effective Date: 29-01-2025
At Venture Technologies, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting the personal data of users of our Ashvadhenu . This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our app.

By using Ashvadhenu, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

1. Information We Collect

We collect the following types of information when you use our app:

Personal Information: This may include your name, email address, and any other information you provide when setting up your account.
Animal Information: This includes details about your livestock, such as breed, health history, feeding schedules, vaccination records, etc.
Usage Data: We collect information on how the app is accessed and used, including your device's IP address, browser type, operating system, and interaction with the app.
2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:

To provide and improve our services: Your information helps us deliver the features and services in the app.
To personalize user experience: We may use the data to customize features, content, and services for you.
To communicate with you: We may use your email address to send you important updates about the app, new features, or customer support messages.
To monitor and analyze app performance: Usage data helps us understand how users interact with the app and improve functionality.
3. Data Security

We use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, but please note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use best practices to protect your data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

4. Data Sharing and Disclosure

We do not share your personal information with third parties except in the following cases:

With your consent: We may share information with third parties if you provide explicit consent.
Service Providers: We may share your data with trusted service providers who assist in the operation of the app (e.g., hosting, data analytics, etc.). These third parties are obligated to use your information only for the purpose of providing services to us.
Legal Requirements: We may disclose your personal information if required by law or in response to a valid legal request by public authorities (e.g., a court or government agency).
5. Retention of Data

We will retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you wish to delete your account or personal data, you may contact us, and we will take appropriate steps to remove the information.

6. Your Data Protection Rights

Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:

The right to access and request copies of your data.
The right to rectify any incorrect or incomplete information.
The right to request the deletion of your personal data (subject to certain exceptions).
The right to object to or restrict processing of your personal data.
The right to withdraw consent at any time where consent is the legal basis for processing.
If you wish to exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the contact details below.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will update the effective date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, or if you wish to exercise your data protection rights, please contact us at:

